<dl id="n10032a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10032a">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10032a"> 32(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> causeway ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n10032a"><li>FW 448.05 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n10032a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n10032a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n10032a">MS BL 47482b-29</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:059 <a name="qA2d" href="../../FF/fdra/qda.htm#qA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qA2d.htm#n10032a">Draft: III&sect;2A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Les Romains se sont montr&eacute;s, comme dans toutes leurs constructions, sup&eacute;rieurs dans l&apos;&eacute;tablissement de leurs voies de communication. Sur une largeur d&apos;environ 20 m&egrave;tres, ces voies pr&eacute;sentaient, dans leur partie m&eacute;diane, une chauss&eacute;e de 6 &agrave; 7 m&egrave;tres, constitu&eacute;e sur une &eacute;paisseur d&apos;un m&egrave;tre, par couches distinctes, et &eacute;taient divis&eacute;es en quatre parties: <i>statumen, rudus, nucleus</i> et <i>summum dorsum;</i> <font color="green">[As with all their constructions, the Romans proved themselves superior in establishing their roads. Approximately twenty metres wide, these roads offered, in their median part, a causeway of six to seven metres. It was one metre thick and its thickness had distinct strata that were divided into four parts: statumen, rudus, nucleus and summum dorsum]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
